name: CVSS v4.0 Qualitative Severity Ratings
definition: CVSS v4.0  using MacroVectors and Interpolation. See https://www.first.org/cvss/specification-document#New-Scoring-System-Development for details

cvss:EQ1:1.0.0.name: Equivalence Set 1
cvss:EQ1:1.0.0.definition: AV/PR/UI with 3 levels specified in Table 24

values.name: Low
values.definition: 2: AV:P or not(AV:N or PR:N or UI:N)

values.name: Medium
values.definition: 1: (AV:N or PR:N or UI:N) and not (AV:N and PR:N and UI:N) and not AV:P

cvss:EQ2:1.0.0.name: Equivalence Set 2
cvss:EQ2:1.0.0.definition: AC/AT with 2 levels specified in Table 25

cvss:EQ3:1.0.0.name: Equivalence Set 3
cvss:EQ3:1.0.0.definition: VC/VI/VA with 3 levels specified in Table 26

values.name: Medium
values.definition: 1: not (VC:H and VI:H) and (VC:H or VI:H or VA:H)

cvss:EQ4:1.0.0.name: Equivalence Set 4
cvss:EQ4:1.0.0.definition: SC/SI/SA with 3 levels specified in Table 27

values.name: Low
values.definition: 2: not (MSI:S or MSA:S) and not (SC:H or SI:H or SA:H)

values.name: Medium
values.definition: 1: not (MSI:S or MSA:S) and (SC:H or SI:H or SA:H)

cvss:EQ5:1.0.0.name: Equivalence Set 5
cvss:EQ5:1.0.0.definition: E with 3 levels specified in Table 28

cvss:EQ6:1.0.0.name: Equivalence Set 6
cvss:EQ6:1.0.0.definition: VC/VI/VA+CR/CI/CA with 2 levels specified in Table 29

values.name: Low
values.definition: 1: not (CR:H and VC:H) and not (IR:H and VI:H) and not (AR:H and VA:H)

values.name: High
values.definition: 0: (CR:H and VC:H) or (IR:H and VI:H) or (AR:H and VA:H)
